###
# ASP.NET Core Web API Tutorial - Sample HTTP Requests
# Use with VS Code REST Client extension or similar tools

###
# 1. CONTROLLER API (TodoItems) - Default port 7000/5000
###

### Get all todos
GET https://localhost:7000/api/TodoItems

### Get specific todo
GET https://localhost:7000/api/TodoItems/1

### Create new todo
POST https://localhost:7000/api/TodoItems
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Learn ASP.NET Core Web API",
  "isComplete": false
}

### Create another todo
POST https://localhost:7000/api/TodoItems
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Implement MongoDB API",
  "isComplete": true
}

### Update todo
PUT https://localhost:7000/api/TodoItems/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Learn ASP.NET Core Web API (Updated)",
  "isComplete": true
}

### Delete todo
DELETE https://localhost:7000/api/TodoItems/1

###
# 2. MONGODB API (Books) - Default port 7001/5001
###

### Get all books
GET https://localhost:7001/api/Books

### Create new book
POST https://localhost:7001/api/Books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookName": "Clean Code",
  "author": "Robert C. Martin",
  "category": "Programming",
  "price": 45.99
}

### Create another book
POST https://localhost:7001/api/Books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookName": "The Pragmatic Programmer",
  "author": "David Thomas, Andrew Hunt",
  "category": "Programming",
  "price": 39.95
}

### Create web development book
POST https://localhost:7001/api/Books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookName": "ASP.NET Core in Action",
  "author": "Andrew Lock",
  "category": "Web Development",
  "price": 49.99
}

### Update book (replace {id} with actual MongoDB ObjectId)
PUT https://localhost:7001/api/Books/{id}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "{id}",
  "bookName": "Clean Code - Updated",
  "author": "Robert C. Martin",
  "category": "Software Engineering",
  "price": 47.99
}

### Delete book (replace {id} with actual MongoDB ObjectId)
DELETE https://localhost:7001/api/Books/{id}

